Case Study 1: FlyRank Machine Learning Internship

The Problem: Content teams have thousands of decaying pages but zero capacity to audit them all manually. They are guessing what to fix first.

What I Did: I ignored static SQL rules and built a Machine Learning ranking pipeline (Refresh Opportunity Scoring). I framed it as a Supervised Binary Classification task to process 90-day historical data and find hidden decay patterns.

The Outcome: A dynamically ranked queue based on real search signals, letting reviewers spend their limited time only on the top 50 pages with the highest recovery potential.

Case Study 2: Şefim Temiz (R&D Project)

The Problem: We needed a system that could automatically recognize various hospitality and service items through machine learning and present this data seamlessly to end users.

What I Did: Working with my teammates Furkan Atalay and Ferhat Yıldız, under the guidance of Doç. Dr. Ömer Faruk Alçin, I tackled the hardest part: training a custom ML model using Python to accurately identify service items. We then integrated this backend intelligence with a responsive frontend built entirely in React.

The Outcome: We successfully bridged advanced image recognition logic with a clean UI, winning 3rd place in the Engineering and Basic Sciences category at the 5th R&D Project Market organized by the Anatolian Universities Union.

Case Study 3: Smart Glasses V2 Validation

The Problem: After training the second version of a smart glasses ML model, we saw an unexpected drop in accuracy that automated tests couldn't pinpoint.

What I Did: I paused the pipeline. To force a human-in-the-loop review, I organized a manual verification protocol and divided a massive dataset of 22,000 images equally among my peers (Taha, Burak, Kaan, and Türker).

The Outcome: We successfully manually verified the dataset, found the noise causing the drop, and established a clean baseline for the next training round.

